n\n4. complete-work\n\nSince the user has provided a detailed spec, I should first invoke the create-plan skill to generate an implementation plan based on the provided requirements, then execute it. The create-plan skill transforms an atomic feature definition into a concrete execution plan (plan.md), and I should use it whenever I have a clear feature definition and need to create an execution roadmap.\n\nGiven the user's explicit and detailed requirements, the planning step is necessary to structure the implementation approach.","signature":"97a8e9239dc008ffb367f393d14e7673029021e09e2961f69a7fb9b028f94648"}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":603,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":57103,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e8ed865-078c-4fea-8f21-00b59c62bf26","uuid":"f700efdc-0283-4b9c-8b76-33466f47f955"}
