{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"call_function_fa6woud8nocq_2","type":"tool_result","content":"1\t# Distributed Order Management System\n2\t\n3\tA distributed order management system with two independent services communicating via HTTP.\n4\t\n5\t## Architecture\n6\t\n7\tThe system consists of two separate services:\n8\t\n9\t1. **Order Service** (Port 8081)\n10\t   - Handles order CRUD operations\n11\t   - Manages order state machine (pending -> paid -> cancelled)\n12\t   - Calls Inventory Service for stock operations\n13\t   - Uses its own SQLite database (`orders.db`)\n14\t\n15\t2. **Inventory Service** (Port 8082)\n16\t   - Manages product inventory\n17\t   - Handles stock reservation, confirmation, and release\n18\t   - Uses its own SQLite database (`inventory.db`)\n19\t\n20\t```\n21\t┌─────────────────┐         HTTP          ┌─────────────────┐\n22\t│  Order Service  │ ◄─────────────────────► │ Inventory       │\n23\t│  (Port 8081)    │                        │ Service         │\n24\t│                 │                        │ (Port 8082)     │\n25\t│  - orders.db    │                        │  - inventory.db │\n26\t└─────────────────┘                        └─────────────────┘\n27\t```\n28\t\n29\t## Features\n30\t\n31\t- **Create Orders**: Automatically reserves inventory\n32\t- **Pay Orders**: Confirms stock deduction\n33\t- **Cancel Orders**: Releases reserved inventory\n34\t- **Overselling Prevention**: Inventory is atomically reserved\n35\t- **Service Independence**: Services can run and fail independently\n36\t\n37\t## Requirements\n38\t\n39\t- Python 3.10+\n40\t\n41\t## Installation\n42\t\n43\t```bash\n44\t# Install dependencies for both services\n45\tcd order_management_system\n46\t\n47\t# Install Order Service dependencies\n48\tcd order_service\n49\tpip install -r requirements.txt\n50\t\n51\t# Install Inventory Service dependencies\n52\tcd ../inventory_service\n53\tpip install -r requirements.txt\n54\t```\n55\t\n56\tOr install all at once:\n57\t\n58\t```bash\n59\tpip install -r requirements.txt\n60\t```\n61\t\n62\t## Running the Services\n63\t\n64\tYou need to start both services. Open two terminal windows:\n65\t\n66\t**Terminal 1 - Start Inventory Service:**\n67\t```bash\n68\tcd order_management_system/inventory_service\n69\tpython -m uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8082\n70\t```\n71\t\n72\t**Terminal 2 - Start Order Service:**\n73\t```bash\n74\tcd order_management_system/order_service\n75\tpython -m uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8081\n76\t```\n77\t\n78\tBoth services will start with SQLite databases in the `data/` directory.\n79\t\n80\t## API Endpoints\n81\t\n82\t### Order Service (Port 8081)\n83\t\n84\t| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n85\t|--------|----------|-------------|\n86\t| POST | `/orders` | Create a new order |\n87\t| GET | `/orders/{id}` | Get order details |\n88\t| POST | `/orders/{id}/pay` | Pay for an order |\n89\t| POST | `/orders/{id}/cancel` | Cancel an order |\n90\t\n91\t### Inventory Service (Port 8082)\n92\t\n93\t| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n94\t|--------|----------|-------------|\n95\t| POST | `/products` | Create a product with stock |\n96\t| POST | `/products/{id}/stock` | Set product stock |\n97\t| GET | `/products/{id}/stock` | Get stock info |\n98\t| POST | `/products/{id}/reserve` | Reserve stock |\n99\t| POST | `/products/{id}/confirm` | Confirm stock deduction |\n100\t| POST | `/products/{id}/release` | Release reserved stock |\n101\t\n102\t## Example Usage\n103\t\n104\t### 1. Initialize Product Stock\n105\t\n106\t```bash\n107\t# Create a product with 100 units at $25.99 each\n108\tcurl -X POST http://localhost:8082/products \\\n109\t  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n110\t  -d '{\n111\t    \"product_id\": \"PROD-001\",\n112\t    \"name\": \"Widget\",\n113\t    \"price\": 25.99,\n114\t    \"stock\": 100\n115\t  }'\n116\t```\n117\t\n118\t### 2. Check Stock\n119\t\n120\t```bash\n121\tcurl http://localhost:8082/products/PROD-001/stock\n122\t```\n123\t\n124\t### 3. Create an Order\n125\t\n126\t```bash\n127\tcurl -X POST http://localhost:8081/orders \\\n128\t  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n129\t  -d '{\n130\t    \"user_id\": \"USER-001\",\n131\t    \"items\": [{\"product_id\": \"PROD-001\", \"quantity\": 5}]\n132\t  }'\n133\t```\n134\t\n135\tAfter creating an order:\n136\t- Order status is `pending`\n137\t- Inventory is reserved (available decreases, reserved increases)\n138\t- Stock check shows: `available_stock: 95, reserved_stock: 5`\n139\t\n140\t### 4. Pay for the Order\n141\t\n142\t```bash\n143\tcurl -X POST http://localhost:8081/orders/{order_id}/pay\n144\t```\n145\t\n146\tAfter payment:\n147\t- Order status changes to `paid`\n148\t- Inventory is confirmed/deducted\n149\t- Stock check shows: `available_stock: 95, reserved_stock: 0`\n150\t\n151\t### 5. Cancel the Order\n152\t\n153\t```bash\n154\tcurl -X POST http://localhost:8081/orders/{order_id}/cancel\n155\t```\n156\t\n157\tAfter cancellation:\n158\t- Order status changes to `cancelled`\n159\t- Reserved inventory is released\n160\t- Stock check shows: `available_stock: 100, reserved_stock: 0`\n161\t\n162\t## Order Status Flow\n163\t\n164\t```\n165\tpending ──┬──► paid ──► completed\n166\t          │\n167\t          └──► cancelled\n168\t```\n169\t\n170\t- **pending**: Order created, inventory reserved\n171\t- **paid**: Payment confirmed, inventory deducted\n172\t- **cancelled**: Order cancelled, reserved inventory released\n173\t- **completed**: (Future) Order delivered\n174\t\n175\t## Stock Flow\n176\t\n177\t1. **Create Order**: Stock is reserved (available decreases, reserved increases)\n178\t2. **Pay Order**: Reserved stock is converted to actual deduction (total decreases, reserved decreases)\n179\t3. **Cancel Order**: Reserved stock is released back (available increases, reserved decreases)\n180\t\n181\t## Running Tests\n182\t\n183\t### Unit Tests for Inventory Service\n184\t```bash\n185\tcd tests\n186\tpytest test_inventory_service.py -v\n187\t```\n188\t\n189\t### Unit Tests for Order Service\n190\t```bash\n191\tcd tests\n192\tpytest test_order_service.py -v\n193\t```\n194\t\n195\t### Integration Tests\n196\t```bash\n197\t# Start both services first (as shown above)\n198\t# Then run integration tests\n199\tcd tests\n200\tpytest test_integration.py -v\n201\t```\n202\t\n203\t## Error Handling\n204\t\n205\t- **404 Not Found**: Order or product does not exist\n206\t- **400 Bad Request**: Insufficient stock, invalid order state\n207\t- **503 Service Unavailable**: Inventory Service is down when Order Service tries to call it\n208\t\n209\t## Project Structure\n210\t\n211\t```\n212\torder_management_system/\n213\t├── order_service/\n214\t│   ├── main.py              # FastAPI app (port 8081)\n215\t│   ├── models.py            # Pydantic models\n216\t│   ├── database.py          # SQLite for orders\n217\t│   ├── services.py          # Order business logic\n218\t│   ├── inventory_client.py  # HTTP client to Inventory Service\n219\t│   └── requirements.txt\n220\t├── inventory_service/\n221\t│   ├── main.py              # FastAPI app (port 8082)\n222\t│   ├── models.py            # Pydantic models\n223\t│   ├── database.py          # SQLite for inventory\n224\t│   ├── services.py          # Inventory business logic\n225\t│   └── requirements.txt\n226\t├── tests/\n227\t│   ├── test_inventory_service.py\n228\t│   ├── test_order_service.py\n229\t│   └── test_integration.py\n230\t├── data/                    # SQLite databases (created at runtime)\n231\t├── requirements.txt\n232\t└── README.md\n233\t```\n234\t\n235\t## Key Design Decisions\n236\t\n237\t1. **Separate Databases**: Each service has its own database to ensure independence\n238\t2. **HTTP Communication**: Services communicate via HTTP, not direct database access\n239\t3. **Stock Reservation Pattern**: Inventory is reserved before order creation to prevent overselling\n240\t4. **Two-Phase Commit**: Stock operations use reserve -> confirm/release pattern for consistency\n241\t5. **Graceful Degradation**: If Inventory Service is down, Order Service returns 503 but keeps its own state"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6e8ed865-078c-4fea-8f21-00b59c62bf26","uuid":"be6c2573-6386-4bc7-99b6-83a8f7f82c03","timestamp":"2026-04-18T11:27:03.037Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/josh_folder/harness-pro-for-vibe/harness-blogs/order-management-system/README.md","content":"# Distributed Order Management System\n\nA distributed order management system with two independent services communicating via HTTP.\n\n## Architecture\n\nThe system consists of two separate services:\n\n1. **Order Service** (Port 8081)\n   - Handles order CRUD operations\n   - Manages order state machine (pending -> paid -> cancelled)\n   - Calls Inventory Service for stock operations\n   - Uses its own SQLite database (`orders.db`)\n\n2. **Inventory Service** (Port 8082)\n   - Manages product inventory\n   - Handles stock reservation, confirmation, and release\n   - Uses its own SQLite database (`inventory.db`)\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐         HTTP          ┌─────────────────┐\n│  Order Service  │ ◄─────────────────────► │ Inventory       │\n│  (Port 8081)    │                        │ Service         │\n│                 │                        │ (Port 8082)     │\n│  - orders.db    │                        │  - inventory.db │\n└─────────────────┘                        └─────────────────┘\n```\n\n## Features\n\n- **Create Orders**: Automatically reserves inventory\n- **Pay Orders**: Confirms stock deduction\n- **Cancel Orders**: Releases reserved inventory\n- **Overselling Prevention**: Inventory is atomically reserved\n- **Service Independence**: Services can run and fail independently\n\n## Requirements\n\n- Python 3.10+\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\n# Install dependencies for both services\ncd order_management_system\n\n# Install Order Service dependencies\ncd order_service\npip install -r requirements.txt\n\n# Install Inventory Service dependencies\ncd ../inventory_service\npip install -r requirements.txt\n```\n\nOr install all at once:\n\n```bash\npip install -r requirements.txt\n```\n\n## Running the Services\n\nYou need to start both services. Open two terminal windows:\n\n**Terminal 1 - Start Inventory Service:**\n```bash\ncd order_management_system/inventory_service\npython -m uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8082\n```\n\n**Terminal 2 - Start Order Service:**\n```bash\ncd order_management_system/order_service\npython -m uvicorn main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8081\n```\n\nBoth services will start with SQLite databases in the `data/` directory.\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n### Order Service (Port 8081)\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| POST | `/orders` | Create a new order |\n| GET | `/orders/{id}` | Get order details |\n| POST | `/orders/{id}/pay` | Pay for an order |\n| POST | `/orders/{id}/cancel` | Cancel an order |\n\n### Inventory Service (Port 8082)\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| POST | `/products` | Create a product with stock |\n| POST | `/products/{id}/stock` | Set product stock |\n| GET | `/products/{id}/stock` | Get stock info |\n| POST | `/products/{id}/reserve` | Reserve stock |\n| POST | `/products/{id}/confirm` | Confirm stock deduction |\n| POST | `/products/{id}/release` | Release reserved stock |\n\n## Example Usage\n\n### 1. Initialize Product Stock\n\n```bash\n# Create a product with 100 units at $25.99 each\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8082/products \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"product_id\": \"PROD-001\",\n    \"name\": \"Widget\",\n    \"price\": 25.99,\n    \"stock\": 100\n  }'\n```\n\n### 2. Check Stock\n\n```bash\ncurl http://localhost:8082/products/PROD-001/stock\n```\n\n### 3. Create an Order\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8081/orders \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"user_id\": \"USER-001\",\n    \"items\": [{\"product_id\": \"PROD-001\", \"quantity\": 5}]\n  }'\n```\n\nAfter creating an order:\n- Order status is `pending`\n- Inventory is reserved (available decreases, reserved increases)\n- Stock check shows: `available_stock: 95, reserved_stock: 5`\n\n### 4. Pay for the Order\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8081/orders/{order_id}/pay\n```\n\nAfter payment:\n- Order status changes to `paid`\n- Inventory is confirmed/deducted\n- Stock check shows: `available_stock: 95, reserved_stock: 0`\n\n### 5. Cancel the Order\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST http://localhost:8081/orders/{order_id}/cancel\n```\n\nAfter cancellation:\n- Order status changes to `cancelled`\n- Reserved inventory is released\n- Stock check shows: `available_stock: 100, reserved_stock: 0`\n\n## Order Status Flow\n\n```\npending ──┬──► paid ──► completed\n          │\n          └──► cancelled\n```\n\n- **pending**: Order created, inventory reserved\n- **paid**: Payment confirmed, inventory deducted\n- **cancelled**: Order cancelled, reserved inventory released\n- **completed**: (Future) Order delivered\n\n## Stock Flow\n\n1. **Create Order**: Stock is reserved (available decreases, reserved increases)\n2. **Pay Order**: Reserved stock is converted to actual deduction (total decreases, reserved decreases)\n3. **Cancel Order**: Reserved stock is released back (available increases, reserved decreases)\n\n## Running Tests\n\n### Unit Tests for Inventory Service\n```bash\ncd tests\npytest test_inventory_service.py -v\n```\n\n### Unit Tests for Order Service\n```bash\ncd tests\npytest test_order_service.py -v\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n```bash\n# Start both services first (as shown above)\n# Then run integration tests\ncd tests\npytest test_integration.py -v\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n- **404 Not Found**: Order or product does not exist\n- **400 Bad Request**: Insufficient stock, invalid order state\n- **503 Service Unavailable**: Inventory Service is down when Order Service tries to call it\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\norder_management_system/\n├── order_service/\n│   ├── main.py              # FastAPI app (port 8081)\n│   ├── models.py            # Pydantic models\n│   ├── database.py          # SQLite for orders\n│   ├── services.py          # Order business logic\n│   ├── inventory_client.py  # HTTP client to Inventory Service\n│   └── requirements.txt\n├── inventory_service/\n│   ├── main.py              # FastAPI app (port 8082)\n│   ├── models.py            # Pydantic models\n│   ├── database.py          # SQLite for inventory\n│   ├── services.py          # Inventory business logic\n│   └── requirements.txt\n├── tests/\n│   ├── test_inventory_service.py\n│   ├── test_order_service.py\n│   └── test_integration.py\n├── data/                    # SQLite databases (created at runtime)\n├── requirements.txt\n└── README.md\n```\n\n## Key Design Decisions\n\n1. **Separate Databases**: Each service has its own database to ensure independence\n2. **HTTP Communication**: Services communicate via HTTP, not direct database access\n3. **Stock Reservation Pattern**: Inventory is reserved before order creation to prevent overselling\n4. **Two-Phase Commit**: Stock operations use reserve -> confirm/release pattern for consistency\n5. **Graceful Degradation**: If Inventory Service is down, Order Service returns 503 but keeps its own state","numLines":241,"startLine":1,"totalLines":241}}}
